summary: This is an email exchange between FBI agents regarding travel to Florida to interview victims following Jeffrey Epstein's arrest and indictment. The New York agents inform Tampa agents they will be interviewing approximately 25 victims, with two located in Winter Garden and Palm Harbor areas.

persons.name: Sean
persons.context: Sends email from FBI New York informing Tampa agents about travel to Florida to interview Epstein victims following his arrest and indictment.

events.title: FBI plans victim interviews in Florida
events.description: FBI agents from New York plan to travel to Florida to interview approximately 25 victims of Jeffrey Epstein following his arrest and indictment.

events.title: Scheduled victim interviews begin
events.description: FBI agents plan to begin interviewing Epstein victims in Florida, starting the day after this email exchange.

keyFacts: FBI agents from New York were traveling to Florida to interview approximately 25 victims of Jeffrey Epstein following his arrest and indictment.
Most victims were located in the Miami/West Palm Beach area, with two specific victims believed to be in Winter Garden and Palm Harbor.
The email exchange occurred on July 9, 2019, with interviews scheduled to begin the following day.
The communication shows coordination between FBI New York and Tampa field offices regarding victim interviews in Florida.
